create a Dockerfile
Write commands in it

FROM node:14                     // this is about version
WORKDIR /app                     // now we are creating a docker image and seeting up a directory for it named "app"
COPY package.json /app           // now copy all the dependencies from package.json to "app"
RUN npm install                  // it installs all dependencies to run application in "app" folder
COPY . /app          


then write command on terminal -> sudo docker build -t node-docker-tutorial .
                                  // -t tagging docker image with name => node-docker-tutorial
next command                   -> sudo docker run -it -p 9000:3000 node-docker-tutorial      
                                  // -p for port
                                  // this 9000:3000 is 9000 to 3000 mapping    (port_which_we_want:port_which_is_running)

now hit local:9000 in the browser

now to run docker in detached mode (in background)
sudo docker run -d -p 9000:3000 node-doker-tutorial      --> to get image id


now type -> sudo docker ps // to see running container